+## 3) Subida por lotes — `POST /api/v1/images/batch` (máx. 20)
+
+```bash
+curl -X POST $BASE/api/v1/images/batch \
+  -H "X-API-Key: $API_KEY" \
+  -F "files=@a.jpg" -F "files=@b.png" -F "group_id=lote1"
+```
+```python
+files = [("files", open("a.jpg","rb")), ("files", open("b.png","rb"))]
+r = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/v1/images/batch", headers=HEADERS,
+                  files=files, data={"group_id": "lote1"})
+# o por URLs (JSON):
+r = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/v1/images/batch", headers=HEADERS,
+                  json={"image_urls": ["https://e.com/1.jpg","https://e.com/2.jpg"]})
+```
