+## 5) Búsqueda por similitud — `POST /api/v1/search/similar`
+
+Campos: `file|image_url|image_path`, `limit` (1–50, def 10), `threshold` (0–1),
+`group_id` (opcional).
+
+```bash
+curl -X POST $BASE/api/v1/search/similar \
+  -H "X-API-Key: $API_KEY" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"image_url":"https://ejemplo.com/foto.jpg","limit":10,"threshold":0.8}'
+```
+```python
+r = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/v1/search/similar", headers=HEADERS,
+                  json={"image_url": "https://ejemplo.com/foto.jpg",
+                        "limit": 10, "threshold": 0.8})
+```
+
+---
+
+## 6) Plagio — `POST /api/v1/search/plagiarism`
+
+Campos: `file|image_url`, `similarity_threshold` (def 0.90, clamp 0.5–1.0),
+`limit` (1–20), `group_id`.
+
+```bash
+curl -X POST $BASE/api/v1/search/plagiarism \
+  -H "X-API-Key: $API_KEY" -F "file=@imagen.jpg" -F "similarity_threshold=0.9"
+```
+```python
+with open("imagen.jpg","rb") as f:
+    r = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/v1/search/plagiarism", headers=HEADERS,
+                      files={"file": f}, data={"similarity_threshold": "0.9"})
+```
+
