+## 8) Reverse Image Search — `POST /api/v1/patents/reverse-image`
+
+Determina si la imagen aparece en otras páginas (Google Lens vía SerpApi).
+Acepta `image_url`, o `file`/`image_path` (se sube temporalmente y se pasa la URL
+pública al proveedor → requiere `SEAWEEDFS_PUBLIC_URL` accesible). `num_results` (≤50).
+
+```bash
+curl -X POST $BASE/api/v1/patents/reverse-image \
+  -H "X-API-Key: $API_KEY" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"image_url":"https://ejemplo.com/foto.jpg","num_results":5}'
+```
+```python
+r = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/v1/patents/reverse-image", headers=HEADERS,
+                  json={"image_url": "https://ejemplo.com/foto.jpg", "num_results": 5})
+```
+Respuesta (ejemplo, normalizada):
+```json
+{
+  "status": "success",
+  "results": {
+    "found_on_internet": true,
+    "verdict": "LIKELY_PRESENT_ONLINE",
+    "confidence": 0.8,
+    "match_count": 5,
+    "matches": [{"title": "...", "link": "https://...", "source": "...", "thumbnail": "https://..."}],
+    "provider": "serpapi", "engine": "google_lens",
+    "query_image_url": "https://ejemplo.com/foto.jpg",
+    "disclaimer": "Reverse image search is probabilistic: matches indicate a similar image is indexed by the provider; absence of matches does NOT prove the image is not online."
+  },
+  "usage": {"serpapi": {"used": 12, "limit": 250, "remaining": 238, "...": "..."}}
+}
+```
+
